-- Goergl of Austria Wins Women’s Downhill Before Home Fans as Vonn Is Fourth
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-07T15:24:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/goergl-wins-women-s-downhill-hirscher-takes-men-s-giant-slalom.html
Austria’s Elisabeth Goergl won
today’s women’s  World Cup  downhill race, as countryman Marcel
Hirscher captured the men’s giant slalom.  Goergl posted a time of 1 minute, 48.40 seconds in front of
the home fans in Bad Kleinkirchheim to beat  Julia Mancuso  of the
U.S. by 0.16 seconds. Switzerland’s Fabienne Suter was third.  American Lindsay Vonn, who won the first two downhills of
the season, finished fourth. Vonn continues to lead the overall
and downhill season standings.  Men’s World Cup leader Hirscher won by 0.08 seconds in
Adelboden, Switzerland, over teammate Benjamin Raich, with
Italy’s Massimiliano Blardone third. It was his second straight
race victory after capturing the slalom in Zagreb two days ago.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  